      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/12/happy-merry/">Happy, merry</a>
    </h1>
  </header>
  <div class="post-content" itemprop="articleBody">
    <p>The three of us wanted to give you something nice. Unfortunately, all I have is this picture.</p>
<p><a href="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/e5e58-polasx70christmasboys-11.jpg"><img decoding="async" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5419319727672982722" class="alignnone" src="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/e5e58-polasx70christmasboys-11.jpg?w=292" alt="" width="913" height="937" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>But mainly, we wanted to say <span style="font-style: italic;">thank you</span>. You’ve given us so much. This year was a big one, and we couldn’t have done any of it &#8211; no book, no restaurant, nothing &#8211; without you. Thank you for being here, for being there, for every kindness. Thank you for giving us so many reasons to celebrate.</p>
<p>See you in 2010.</p>
