    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Three quarters through your book, and I have two comments.  One, I read alot of recipe-laden memoirs, and I cannot recall any with so high a &#8220;I must make this!&#8221; response ratio as yours.  Two, on the back, a reviewer wrote &#8220;Echoes of M.F.K. Fisher.&#8221; I disagree.  I found Ms. Fisher to be more formal, a stiffer, less accessible, more intimidating author than Molly W. Molly W. reminds me of the late  amazing Laura Colwin, who&#39;s books &#8220;Home Cooking&#8221; and &#8220;More Home Cooking&#8221; are two I HAD to have in hardback, and reread and loan on a regular basis. So if you need a read, Molly W., check those out.  Love your book, can&#39;t wait to cook!</p>
